{{Politics of Puerto Rico}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in [[Puerto Rico]] on 6 November 1994.<ref name=N1>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen, D]] (2005) ''Elections in the Americas: A data handbook, Volume I'', p552 {{ISBN|978-0-19-928357-6}}</ref> Voters were asked whether they approved of two amendments, one to eliminate the absolute right to [[bail]] and the other to increase the number of [[Supreme Court of Puerto Rico|Supreme Court]] judges. Both were rejected by 54% of voters, with a turnout of 62.2%.<ref>Nohlen, p557</ref>
